![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/072a97b7-f1f5-421b-a85d-7dcc90df8620/20240420_143512.jpg)

PWInsider reports TNA has been in preliminary talks with Tess Blanchard about making a return to the company.

It’s not known if this is connected to the “Lights Out” teaser that aired on IMPACT last week.

Tessa Blanchard's time with TNA Wrestling was marked by both success and controversy. She became the Impact World Champion, making history as the first woman to hold the title. However, there were reports of backstage issues, including allegations of bullying and racism. These issues led to her departure from the company amidst some controversy.